---
const checkItems = [
  'Every plugin is free and open source — no paid tiers, ever',
  'One plugin per problem, built to do it well',
  'Anyone can contribute — code, ideas, or donations',
  'No gatekeeping, no "pro" version waiting around the corner',
];
---

<section id="mission" class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12 lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Why We Do This</h2>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          WordPress.org is full of plugins that do the same thing — most of them locking the good parts behind a paywall. The ecosystem shouldn't work like that. We build free alternatives that actually solve the problem, and we keep them alive through community support — donations and code contributions alike.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
          {checkItems.map((item) => (
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center size-6 rounded-full bg-green-100">
                  <svg class="size-4 text-green-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="ml-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">{item}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 lg:mt-0">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 lg:p-10">
          <blockquote class="text-gray-600 italic text-lg leading-relaxed">
            "Bringing back the power of WordPress, one plugin at a time."
          </blockquote>
          <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-100">
            <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Open WP Club</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
